.\pages\PartnerHome\codex-round2-s54.md:29:MY ADDITIONAL POINT: The Settings page has 8 tabs (Profile, Hours, Channels, Hall, Wi-Fi, Languages, Currencies, Contacts). That is already too many tabs for a mobile-first admin panel. Rather than keeping a summary card + CTA in Settings for Contacts, I propose removing the Contacts tab from Settings entirely. This reduces Settings to 7 tabs. But actually, I think we should go further: some of these Settings tabs could also become standalone pages (e.g., Hours could live on its own). What is your view on how many tabs is right for a settings page on mobile?
.\pages\PartnerHome\codex-round2-s54.md:39:Step 1 (NOW): Add 'Settings' and 'Contacts' to the hamburger menu. This is a small code change. The hamburger currently has Profile, Language, Logout О“ГҮГ¶ adding 2 more items is trivial.
